org.gearvrf

Class GVRHybridObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gearvrf.GVRHybridObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GVRBaseShaderManager, GVRBoneWeight, GVRComponent, GVRMaterial, GVRMaterialMap, GVRMesh, GVRPostEffect, GVRPostEffectMap, GVRRenderPass, GVRScene, GVRSceneObject, GVRTexture, GVRTextureCapturer

    public abstract class GVRHybridObject
extends java.lang.Object
    Root of the GVRF object hierarchy. Descendant classes all have native (JNI) implementations; this base class manages the native lifecycles.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      protected static class  GVRHybridObject.CleanupHandlerListManager
      Small class to help descendants keep the number of lists of native cleanup handlers to a minimum.
      protected static interface  GVRHybridObject.NativeCleanupHandler
      Optional after-finalization callback to 'deregister' native pointers.

      • GVRHybridObject

        protected GVRHybridObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                          long nativePointer,
                          java.util.List<GVRHybridObject.NativeCleanupHandler> cleanupHandlers)
        Special constructor, for descendants like GVRCollider that need to 'unregister' instances.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - The current GVRF context
        nativePointer - The native pointer, returned by the native constructor
        cleanupHandlers - Cleanup handler(s).

        Normally, this will be a private static class constant, so that there is only one List per class. Descendants that supply a List and also have descendants that supply a List should use GVRHybridObject.CleanupHandlerListManager to maintain a Map<List<NativeCleanupHandler>, List<NativeCleanupHandler>> whose keys are descendant lists and whose values are unique concatenated lists - see GVRCollider for an example.
